30
00:02:02,990 --> 00:02:07,850
Today, you have a rule which goes by the name of general average.

31
00:02:07,850 --> 00:02:14,200
And the general average is what you do in a situation like this.

32
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:19,260
You figure out what the total value of the cargo of the ship was.

33
00:02:19,260 --> 00:02:22,940
Let&#39;s say the total value was worth $1,000.

34
00:02:22,940 --> 00:02:29,210
What you did is you had to throw $300 worth of cargo overboard--

35
00:02:29,210 --> 00:02:34,050
$300 worth of stone or blocks of marble--

36
00:02:34,050 --> 00:02:39,080
to save the remaining cargo of silk and spices.

37
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:45,370
The remaining cargo doesn&#39;t just thank its lucky stars and count its blessings

38
00:02:45,370 --> 00:02:47,080
all the way to the bank.

39
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,630
Not at all.

40
00:02:48,630 --> 00:02:53,890
We saw 3/10 of the worth of the total cargo was lost.

41
00:02:53,890 --> 00:02:59,440
It was sacrificed in order to save the remaining cargo.

42
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:04,860
The marble was sacrificed in order to save the silk and spices.

43
00:03:04,860 --> 00:03:09,210
Under the law of the sea, the owners of all the cargo

44
00:03:09,210 --> 00:03:14,150
get together under what&#39;s called general average and each of them

45
00:03:14,150 --> 00:03:19,750
ends up with 7/10 of the value of the total cargo.

46
00:03:19,750 --> 00:03:22,790
The people whose cargo was thrown overboard

47
00:03:22,790 --> 00:03:26,210
get 7/10 of the value of theirs.

48
00:03:26,210 --> 00:03:33,070
And the people whose cargo survived get only 7/10 of theirs.

49
00:03:33,070 --> 00:03:37,670
It&#39;s a kind of insurance policy, a sharing of risk.

50
00:03:37,670 --> 00:03:43,440
They all shared the risk, and they all ended up losing proportionately.

51
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:45,540
But nobody lost everything.

52
00:03:45,540 --> 00:03:52,300
Nobody got away without losing something-- well, except for Jonah.

